    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect neighbor cell configuration parsing in gNB\n\n### Summary\nThe `fill_neighbour_cell_configuration` function in `gnb_config.c` was not properly handling neighbor cell configurations due to an incorrect parameter definition and several memory management issues. This caused unexpected behavior when loading neighbor cell configurations.\n\nThe main issues were:\n1. An incorrect parameter in `GNB_NEIGHBOUR_LIST_PARAM_LIST` that didn't belong at that configuration level\n2. Memory leaks when the function was called multiple times\n3. Type mismatch between 64-bit configuration values and 32-bit structure fields\n4. Format string mismatches in logging\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/GNB_APP/gnb_paramdef.h`: Removed incorrect `GNB_CONFIG_STRING_NEIGHBOUR_CELL_PHYSICAL_ID` parameter from `GNB_NEIGHBOUR_LIST_PARAM_LIST`\n- `openair2/GNB_APP/gnb_config.c`: \n  - Added proper memory cleanup before allocations\n  - Fixed type conversion for absoluteFrequencySSB field with bounds checking\n  - Corrected format strings in log messages\n  - Changed from malloc to calloc for better initialization\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a gNB with neighbor cell configurations\n2. Call `fill_neighbour_cell_configuration()` multiple times\n3. Observe memory leaks and potentially incorrect neighbor cell data being loaded\n4. Check logs for incorrectly formatted SSB ARFCN values\n\nThe fix ensures that neighbor cell configurations are properly parsed and loaded without memory leaks or data corruption.\n"
}